<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06259050 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06259050 </ACCESS><CAPTION>  Photo; PHOTO: Reynolds  </CAPTION><LEADPARA>  It was all according to the script when Burt Reynolds tried to heat a babybottle in a microwave oven on the set of &quot;Evening Shade.&quot; The bottle explodedinto flames on cue, and co-star Michael Jeter rushed to the rescue with a propfire extinguisher, according to plan.;   You trivia collectors should make anote that prop fire extinguishers contain not the usual chemicals but the morevisually effective baby powder, a substance that apparently tends to ad lib.When Jeter sprayed the stuff it exploded . . . right in Reynolds' face.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  SCENE INTERRUPTED BY BABY POWDER  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  People.  </MEMO><TEXT>     (We don't believe the fiery properties of baby powder ever have made thenews before, but we must pass over the subject, pleading ignorance of thephysics involved.);   After the powder cleared, Reynolds was ready to go onshooting but the studio chiefs dragged him to Sherman Oaks Hospital and HealthCenter saying they would rather not take chances with the star's well-being.;  The medics calmed the fearful execs by taking one look at Reynolds anddiagnosing singed eyebrows and a good attitude. Then they sent everyone home,presumably to put their baby powder out of the reach of children.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Jim Jeffress; Compiled from Mercury News wire services.  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910915  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Sunday  </DAY><MONTH>  September  </MONTH><PG.COL>  2A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  PHOTO  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  200  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Sunday, September 15, 199100259050,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>